              a(href="http://nashvillesoftwareschool.com/", target="_blank")  Nashville Software School
              | . I may be new to software engineering, but I have years of experience and education in the world of information technology.
              | After completing an undergraduate degree in Computer Science at the University of Lagos in Nigeria,
              | I worked at different levels of IT across two continents, starting with training corporate executives on maximizing the capabilities of Microsoft Excel.
              | And prior to my apprenticeship at Nashville Software School, I managed a centralized framework ensuring data integrity for a financial services firm.
            p
              | Now armed with a full stack web-development training, coupled with a newly discovered love for creating beautiful UX experiences, I want to bridge the gap between functionality and design.
              | When I'm not coding, I can be found reading books(currently slogging through the Game of Thrones series).
              | I consider myself an amateur food conjurer, and an unrepentant foodie with a particular fondness for pancakes and hot cocoa.

